Sure! Here's the recipe for the quick cake with Nescau and Maizena:

Ingredients:

    1 cup of Nescau
    1 cup of Maizena
    1 cup of sugar
    1 cup of milk
    3 eggs
    1 tablespoon of baking powder
    1/2 cup of vegetable oil

Instructions:

1) Preheat your oven to 180°C (350°F).
2) In a large mixing bowl, mix together the Nescau, Maizena, sugar, and baking powder.
3) Add the milk, eggs, and vegetable oil to the bowl and mix everything together until you have a smooth batter.
4) Pour the batter into a greased cake pan.
5) Bake for around 30-35 minutes or until a toothpick inserted into the center of the cake comes out clean.
6) Allow the cake to cool before serving.

And here's the recipe for the chocolate sauce:

Ingredients:

    1 cup of sugar
    1/2 cup of Nescau
    1/2 cup of water
    1 tablespoon of unsalted butter
    1 teaspoon of vanilla extract

Instructions:

1) In a small saucepan, mix together the sugar, Nescau, and water.
2) Heat the mixture over medium heat, stirring constantly until the sugar is completely dissolved.
3) Add the butter to the mixture and stir until it is completely melted.
4) Allow the sauce to cook for a few more minutes until it thickens slightly.
5) Remove from heat and add the vanilla extract. Stir well.
6) Pour the sauce over the cake after it has cooled down a bit and let it cool completely before serving.

This sauce will add a delicious touch of chocolate to the cake and complement the flavor of the Nescau and Maizena. Enjoy!
